      • initRecordCSV

        public void initRecordCSV(String csvRecord)
                   throws RecordException
        Apply to the fields of this record, the formatted values present in the csvRecord parameter. Every value must be separated with the CSVSep.COMMA. A value must be enclosed with CSVEnc.DOUBLE_QUOTE if contains CSVSep.COMMA. Each of the embedded enclosing characters CSVEnc.DOUBLE_QUOTE must be represented by a pair of double-enclosing characters.
        Parameters:
        csvRecord - the formatted csv string
        Throws:
        RecordException - if the the csvRecord is malformed or the formatted csv string obtained from toStringCSV method diff from the csvRecord parameter

      • initRecordCSV

        public void initRecordCSV(String csvRecord,
                          CSVSep sep,
                          String otherSep,
                          CSVEnc enclosing)
                   throws RecordException
        Apply to the fields of this record, the formatted values present in the csvRecord parameter. Every value must be separated with the sep param. If the sep param is null, the default sep is CSVSep.COMMA. Every value can be (or not) enclosed with the enclosing param. If the enclosing param is null, the default enclosing is CSVEnc.DOUBLE_QUOTE. A value must be enclosed if contains the char sep. Inside an eclosed value, each of the embedded enclosing characters must be represented by a pair of double-enclosing characters.
        Parameters:
        csvRecord - the formatted csv string
        sep - the field separator. If null the sep is CSVSep.COMMA
        otherSep - the field separator if sep param is CSVSep.OTHER. Size must be eq 1. If null the sep is CSVSep.COMMA
        enclosing - the enclosing char. If null the enclosing char is CSVEnc.DOUBLE_QUOTE
        Throws:
        RecordException - if the the csvRecord is malformed or the separator size not eq 1 or the formatted csv string obtained from toStringCSV method diff from the csvRecord parameter

      • toStringCSV

        public String toStringCSV()
                   throws RecordException
        Returns a CSV String object representing this record. The returned string is composed with the formatted unpadded value of every field of this record. Every value is separated with the CSVSep.COMMA. The fields aren't enclosing, eccept those which contain the char CSVSep.COMMA. In this case the fields are enclosing with CSVEnc.DOUBLE_QUOTE. Each of the embedded enclosing CSVEnc.DOUBLE_QUOTE characters is represented by a pair of double-enclosing characters.
        Returns:
        a CSV string representation of this record
        Throws:
        RecordException - it the status of this record is ERROR

      • toStringCSV

        public String toStringCSV(CSVSep sep,
                          String otherSep,
                          CSVEnc enclosing,
                          boolean encloseAllFields)
                   throws RecordException
        Returns a CSV String object representing this record. The returned string is composed with the formatted unpadded value of every field of this record. Every value is separated with the sep param. If the sep param is null, the default sep is CSVSep.COMMA. If encloseAllFields is true, every field of the record is enclosed with the enclosing param. If the enclosing param is null, the default enclosing is CSVEnc.DOUBLE_QUOTE. If the encloseAllFields param is false the fields aren't enclosing, eccept they contain the char sep. Each of the embedded char enclosing characters is represented by a pair of double-enclosing characters.
        Parameters:
        sep - the field separator. If null the sep is CSVSep.COMMA
        otherSep - the field separator if sep param is CSVSep.OTHER. Size must be eq 1. If null the default sep is CSVSep.COMMA
        enclosing - the enclosing char. If null the enclosing char is CSVEnc.DOUBLE_QUOTE
        encloseAllFields - if true every field of the record is enclosed with the enclosing char, otherwise only field which contains sep
        Returns:
        a CSV string representation of this record
        Throws:
        RecordException - it the status of this record is ERROR or the separator size not eq 1
